article.headline: USC 76, Santa Barbara 61
article.story:
LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Ebony Hoffman and Jamie Hagiya scored 15
points apiece to lead USC past UC Santa Barbara 76-61 Thursday
night.

Hagiya scored her 15 with 5-of-6 shooting from behind the
3-point line. All of her field goal attempts in the game were
3-pointers.

Hoffman also led the Women of Troy with 10 rebounds. Rometra
Craig added 12 points.

USC (15-11, 11-6 Pacific 10 Conference) shot 52 percent from the
field and 55 percent from behind the 3-point line in the first half
on the way to a 45-26 halftime lead.

The Women of Troy cooled off in the second half, shooting 43
percent to the Gauchos' 48 percent, but maintained a double-digit
lead for the rest of the game.

Lindsay Taylor led UC Santa Barbara (19-6, 13-1 Big West) with
23 points on 9-of-13 shooting. Kristen Mann had 19.
